EPS for Armstrong World Industries Inc (AWI) Expected At $0.69

July 25, 2017 - By reb123z


Investors sentiment increased to 1.29 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.24, from 1.05 in 2016Q3. It increased, as 26 investors sold Armstrong World Industries Inc shares while 44 reduced holdings. 33 funds opened positions while 57 raised stakes. 56.93 million shares or 0.28% less from 57.09 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported.
1.07 million are held by State Street Corp. Fuller Thaler Asset Management reported 1.06% stake. Moreover, Rhumbline Advisers has 0% invested in Armstrong World Industries Inc (NYSE:AWI) for 42,326 shares. Barclays Plc accumulated 42,651 shares. Teachers Retirement Of The State Of Kentucky accumulated 23,866 shares. Foster Dykema Cabot & Ma invested in 5,000 shares or 0.04% of the stock. Gsa Ptnrs Llp reported 15,900 shares. Deutsche Financial Bank Ag owns 0% invested in Armstrong World Industries Inc (NYSE:AWI) for 2,615 shares. Massachusetts Financial Ma stated it has 0.03% of its portfolio in Armstrong World Industries Inc (NYSE:AWI). Northern Trust Corporation reported 0% of its portfolio in Armstrong World Industries Inc (NYSE:AWI). Parallax Volatility Advisers L P owns 646 shares. Emory University owns 40,029 shares. Arlington Value Capital Limited Co has invested 0.95% in Armstrong World Industries Inc (NYSE:AWI). Oxford Asset has invested 0.02% of its portfolio in Armstrong World Industries Inc (NYSE:AWI). D E Shaw holds 0.06% or 898,488 shares in its portfolio.
Investors wait Armstrong World Industries Inc (NYSE:AWI) to report on July, 31 before the open. its quarterly earnings Wall Street analysts expect $0.69 EPS, up $0.13 or 23.21 % from last year’s $0.56 same quarter earnings. This translates into $36.36M profit for AWI giving the stock a 16.50 P/E. This is assuming the current $0.69 EPS is accurate. Armstrong World Industries Inc’s Wall Street analysts see 25.45 % EPS growth, taking into account the $0.55 EPS reproted in the previous quarter, About 281,663 shares traded. Armstrong World Industries Inc (NYSE:AWI) has risen 6.90% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 9.80% the S&P500.






